Cell.Text: [S] Telisha's lantern isn't lit, it's not like her to leave the Tavern without telling me anything.

[S] This is bad. She's completely oblivious of the dangers that lay ahead of her. | I'm well aware of the cave she's talking about, as it's the very same one that I found the enchanted lanterns in sometime ago. | Let us hope she hasn't set out to get the ring by herself, as the cave she speaks of is now infested with bandits. | It was a catastrophic error on my part - entrusting the ring to her, I've put someone in harms way, but I haven't time to dwell on it right now. | We must leave immediately, however, I could also stay behind instead, just in case she returns safely.
I have received a letter from Telisha.
Have you found any clues as to Telisha's whereabouts?
No. I haven't found anything yet.
[S] G|I'm going to search the perimeter of the town. I suggest you do the same. Hopefully she hasn't gone too far.
[S] We need to hurry. Let's go.
You stay here, I'll handle this myself.
[S] Alright then. I'll stay here at the tavern for now. She may be back soon. I'll come and get you if she returns.
Enchanted lanterns? What are you talking about?

I found a pair of enchanted lanterns in a nearby cave a while back. Telisha and I both have one each. They will only stay lit when the owner is at home. | One sits on the railing here at the tavern, the other is on a barrel outside of the lumber camp. | We use them as a convenient way of tracking each other at a glance.
My name is Eivind Lockfell, I'm friends with Telisha Ria, who works at this tavern. I've definitely seen you in there before. So, have you seen her?
